Some information about SHC (Snake Human Conflict) app: 
 Fear of snakes found among humans for its external structure and nature of its movement. This is why people are arrogant to kill snakes as soon as they see them. In addition, every year about 100,000 (One Lakh) people are bitten by snakes in Bangladesh. Among them, about 6000 (Six Thousand) people die. The main purpose of this app is to keep people and snakes away from exchanging accurate information about snakes.
 Instructions: 

1. You have to turn on the location of your mobile phone; 

2. Snake pictures and place names should be given in details; 

3. You must have to maintain a safe distance while taking pictures of a live snake; 

4. This app will not collect any personal information from your mobile phone; 

5. The information you provided will only be used for research purposes. Shall not be used for any commercial purpose or transferred to any third party; 

6. The mobile number you provided may be used for communication purpose; 


If you agree with the above instructions, click the "Agree" button. 

For any changes, refinements and suggestions please contact: 

shcbangladeh@gmail.com
